Sentencas: Cathode thickness plays a major role in establishing an active area for an oxygen reduction reaction in energy converter devices, such as solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Layering Optimization of the SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 Composite Cathode

Sentencas: In this work, we prepared SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-delta-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite cathodes with different layers (1x, 3x, 5x, 7x, and 9x layer).
Titulo: Layering Optimization of the SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 Composite Cathode

Sentencas: The microstructural and electrochemical performance of each cell was then explored through scanning electron microscopy and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS).
Titulo: Layering Optimization of the SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 Composite Cathode

Sentencas: EIS analysis showed that the area-specific resistance (ASR) decreased from 0.65 omega cm(2) to 0.12 omega cm(2) with the increase in the number of layers from a 1x to a 7x.
Titulo: Layering Optimization of the SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 Composite Cathode

Sentencas: However, the ASR started to slightly increase at the 9x layer to 2.95 omega cm(2) due to a higher loss of electrode polarization resulting from insufficient gas diffusion and transport.
Titulo: Layering Optimization of the SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 Composite Cathode

Sentencas: Therefore, increasing the number of cathode layers could increase the performance of the cathode by enlarging the active area for the reaction up to the threshold point.
Titulo: Layering Optimization of the SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 Composite Cathode
